data.text:
May Fortescue, actress, singer and actor-manager, theatrical portrait in black, beaded gown with satin puff shoulders. May Fortescue was a protegee of the playwright Ws Gilbert, previously a member of the D'Oyly Carte Opera Company from 1881 to 1883, leaving the company following her engagement to Arthur William Cairns, Lord Garmoyle. Date: 1895. Mary Evans Picture Library makes available wonderful images created for people to enjoy over the centuries. Â© Illustrated London News Ltd/Mary Evans
